subunit_name: Systems of 2 linear equations in 2 variables

source: In triangle \(ABC\), angle \(A\) measures \(40^{\circ}\) and angle \(B\) measures \(60^{\circ}\). What is the measure of angle \(C\)?

\(F = 2000(1.05)^{\frac{Q}{4}}\) \ The equation above models the total number of followers, F, on a social media account Q quarter years after the 2 months. Based on the model, which of the following statements are true?
correct: The number of subscribers increases by \(5\) percent each quarter year
false_1: The number of subscribers increases by \(5\) percent each year
false_2: The total number of subscribers increases by \(2000\) each quarter year
false_3: The total number of subscribers increases by \(2000\) each year

subunit_name: Ratios, rates, proportional relationships, and units
source: A car travels \(180\) miles in \(4\) hours. What is the average speed of the car in miles per hour?
The area of a circle is \(64\pi\) square units. What is the radius of the circle?
The function \(f\) is defined by the equation \(f(x)=7x+2\). What is the value of \(f(x)\) when \(x=4\)?

A teacher is creating an assignment worth \(70\) points. The assignment will consist of questions worth \(1\) point and questions worth \(3\) points. Which equation represents this situation, where \(x\) represents the number of \(1\)-point questions and \(y\) represents the number of \(3\)-point questions?
Given a circle centered at \((-4,4)\) with a radius of 9, what is the equation of the circle?
Right triangles \(LMN\) and \(PQR\) are similar, where \(L\) and \(M\) correspond to \(P\) and \(Q\), respectively. Angle \(M\) has a measure of \(53^{\circ}\). What is the measure of angle Q?

subunit_name: Systems of 2 linear equations in 2 variables
source: \(48x-72y = 30y+24\) \(ry=\frac{1}{6}-16x\) In the given system of equations, \(r\) is a constant. If the system has no solution, what is the value of \(r\)?

subunit_name: Ratios, rates, proportional relationships, and units
source: Bacteria are growing in a liquid growth medium. There were \(300000\) cells per milliliter during an initial observation. The number of cells per milliliter doubles every \(3\) hours. How many cells per milliliter will there be \(15\) hours after the initial observation?
\(\sqrt{x}\cdot\sqrt{\frac{y^{5}}{x^{3}}}\) Which of the following is equivalent to the given expression for all positive values of x and y?

subunit_name: Evaluating statistical claims: observational studies and experiments
source: A school district wants to conduct a sample survey to determine the average number of sports played by high school seniors in the district. Which of the following survey methods is most likely to produce valid results?
correct: The district surveys \(500\) randomly selected high school seniors in the district.
false_1: The district selects one high school in the district and surveys all of its students.
false_2: The district surveys every tenth student to enter the football stadium at the district championship game.
false_3: The district surveys \(500\) randomly selected high school seniors in the district who play baseball.

source: A washing machine is being redesigned to handle a greater volume of water. One part is a pipe with a radius of \(3\) centimetes (cm) and a length of \(11\)cm it gets replaced with a pipe of radius \(4\)cm and the same length. The new pipe can hold \(w\pi\) more cubic centimeters \(cm^{3}\) of water than the old pipe, where w is a constant. What is the value of w?

subunit_name: Ratios, rates, proportional relationships, and units
source: A neighborhood consists of a 2-hectare park and a 35-hectare residential area. The total number of trees in the neighborhood is 3934. The equation \(2x y + 35 = 3934\) represents this situation. Which of the following is the best interpretation of \(x\) in this context?
correct: The average number of trees per hectare in the park
false_1: The average number of trees per hectare in the residential area
false_2: The total number of trees in the park
false_3: The total number of trees in the residential area
